{"id":1661,"date":"2011-11-29T06:15:58","date_gmt":"2011-11-29T02:15:58","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.dailyhadithonline.com\/?p=1661"},"modified":"2025-03-03T10:39:09","modified_gmt":"2025-03-03T06:39:09","slug":"final-dua-before-sleep-fitrah","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2011\/11\/29\/final-dua-before-sleep-fitrah\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Dua: Your final supplication before sleep"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Al-Bara&#8217; ibn &#8216;Azib reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201c<strong>When you go to sleep, perform ablution as for your prayer, then lie down on your right side and say: O Allah, I submit my face to You, I entrust my affair to You, and I commit myself to You, in hope and in fear of You. There is no refuge or place of safety but with You. I believe in the Book You have revealed, and in the Prophet You have sent.<\/strong>&#8220;<strong>\u00a0<\/strong>Then, the Prophet said, &#8220;<strong>Make these your last words. If you died in this night of yours, you will have died upon pure nature<\/strong>.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 6311, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 2710<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <b><i>Muttafaqun Alayhi\u00a0<\/i><\/b>(authenticity agreed upon) according to Al-Bukhari and Muslim<\/p>\n<p align=\"right\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0628\u064e\u0631\u064e\u0627\u0621\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0639\u064e\u0627\u0632\u0650\u0628\u064d \u0623\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0651 \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u0644\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647 \u0639\u0644\u064a\u0647 \u0648\u0633\u0644\u0645 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0625\u0650\u0630\u064e\u0627 \u0623\u064e\u062e\u064e\u0630\u0652\u062a\u064e \u0645\u064e\u0636\u0652\u062c\u064e\u0639\u064e\u0643\u064e \u0641\u064e\u062a\u064e\u0648\u064e\u0636\u064e\u0651